<item>
            <title>[LU-15082] osp can stop refreshing statfs data</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15082</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;there is a race between osp_statfs_timer_cb() and osp_precreate_thread() when the timer callback is called just before statfs data gets stale (according to @opd_statfs_fresh_till) and then woken osp_precreate_thread() finds statfs data valid. essentially it&apos;s early-wakeup leading stale statfs data. if no creates happen on this OST for a reason (e.g. current space usage), then statfs data won&apos;t be refreshed for a long time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
